{
  "doc_id": "23219",
  "text": "Inspired by statistics research and computer vision theory, Wang et al. [CITATION_1] proposed a small target detection method utilizing least squares support vector machine (LS-SVM). Li et al. [CITATION_2] employed the local steering kernel (LSK) to encode the infrared image patch and proposed a local adaptive contrast measure based on regularized LSK reconstruction. Moreover, Gao et al. [CITATION_3] developed their IPI model by taking the temporal cue into consideration and presented a statistical model based on the mixture of Gaussians (MoG) and the Markov random field (MRF). In addition to the state-of-the-art studies, there are still many other algorithms for detecting dim-small targets, such as algorithms based on the statistical regression [CITATION_4] , manifold learning [CITATION_5] , the nearest neighbor classifier [CITATION_6] , neural networks [CITATION_7] , etc.",
